721007f.title: Manhattan: Lexington Avenue - 46th Street (East)
721007f.text:
Lexington Avenue, north from E. 46th Street, as photo-
Eraphed from the Graybar Building (No. 420 Lexington Avenue)
showing this locale and the unfinished Waldorf-Astoria hotel.
1931
Ewing Galloway
NO REPRODUCTIONS

713249f.title: Manhattan: 46th Street (East) - Lexington Avenue
713249f.text:
A rear view of 131 East 46th Street, adjoining the N. E. corner
of Lexington Avenue.
January 8, 1915
Wurts Brother, Photographers
NO REPRODUCTIONS

721009f-c.title: Manhattan: Lexington Avenue - 46th Street (East)
721009f-c.text:
Lexington Avenue, north from E. 46th Street (intersection
in foreground ), showing north of 47th Street the new hotel zone
with its Lexington, Shelton, Montclair and Beverly on the east
side of sare. The lower block (46th - 47th Street ) front in
conjunction with adjoining buildigs will be cleared (with the
excention of a 20 foot parcel at No. 493) and the space improved
with a 1 atory commercial buildinm to contain 11 stores, and an
automobile parking lot. This will cost ~150,000. A fuller
account was carried in the New York Sun of December 19, 1938.
View No. 3 shows only this limited area. Note in No. 1, the
Grand Central Valace oprosite same.
March 28, 1938.
View 2: July 24, 19E2
View 3: May 21, 1928.
P.L. Sperr
NO REPRODUTTIONS.
